      "message": "I think we can do this and still keep error prone happy. If not, I would suppress it. The [intent](https://errorprone.info/bugpattern/FloggerStringConcatenation) is to avoid work at the logging site and concatenating two strings isn\u0027t the kind of work they\u0027re trying to flag.\n```suggestion\n      String message \u003d \"Error while walking directory\";\n      if (isMultiPrimary() \u0026\u0026 e instanceof NoSuchFileException) {\n        logger.atFine().log(\n            \"%s %s (expected regularly with multi-primaries and distributor enabled)\",\n            message, path);\n      } else {\n        logger.atSevere().withCause(e).log(\"%s %s\", message, path);\n```",
